commits.message:
Show fork of a repository - if it exists

The primaryKey is removed, so the repository is always fetched from the API. This is required since the `parent` property on a repository hash is only returned by the API when the repository is requested explicitly. Asking the API for a list of repositories, will not contain this property ...

This can be fixed by reloading the repository in the store.

milestone.description:
First working version of the dashboard. Should offer the following features:

- show repositories of an user
- show followers of an user
- show followed users
- show watched repositories
- show events for a repository
- show events for an user
